        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Windows Server 2003'); ?>
        <p><strong>Windows Server 2003</strong> (sometimes referred to as <strong>Win2K3</strong>) is a server <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Operation System', 'IT'); ?> produced by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft', 'C'); ?>, released on 24 April 2003. An updated version, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows Server 2003 R2', 'WIS'); ?>, was released to manufacturing on 6 December 2005. Its successor, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows Server 2008', 'WIS'); ?>, was released on 4 February 2008. It is based on <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows XP', 'WIN'); ?>, basically becoming an enhanced version of XP. According to Microsoft, Windows Server 2003 is more scalable and delivers better performance than its predecessor, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows Server 2000', 'WIS'); ?>.</p>
        <p><?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows Vista', 'WIN'); ?>, as shipped, was developed based solely on Windows Server 2003 source code.</p>
